      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VINIES JOLT (8) kicked off her career in good style two weeks ago, beaten a head into second over 1730m at Bathurst. Drawn to enjoy a nice run, with luck possibly playing a role at some point. Won't find this any harder and she can go right on with the job. STAY LUCKY (2) finished third at her most recent outing, beaten 6 metres, in a far better performance at Canberra over 1770m when second-up from a break. Likely to get all the favours from this nice draw. Tackles a similar assignment and she can find the winners' circle. CLASSYNFABULOUS (1) is a three-year-old filly from the Amanda Turnbull yard on debut. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Will be ready to run a big race. WINDY HILL ABBEY (11) finished fourth two runs ago then broke and finished a distant last over 1730m at Bathurst at the latest appearance. Draws out a little on the second line and may need luck at some point. Live chance in a similar assignment.",
